<HEADLINE> Pak Government Vows to Pursue Loan Defaulters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Finance Minister
Sartaj Aziz Saturday asked all banks and financial institutions to
pursue loan defaulters and warned of dire consequences after the
expiry of a July 10 deadline.
</P>
<P>
Sartaj told a press conference here that all defaulters, as
announced by Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif on Thursday, must pay off
their loans or face strict action after four weeks.
</P>
<P>
To a question about specific steps taken by the government to
recover 140 billion rupees (about 3.2 billion U.S. dollars) stuck
up with the defaulters, he said, "We have not yet decided the
action plan against the defaulters."
</P>
<P>
He said the State Bank of Pakistan has been asked to collect
the new list of defaulters from banks in the light of which an
action plan against defaulters will be formulated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
