<HEADLINE> Police at Grassroots Substations Key to Public Security: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Minister of Public Security Jia
Chunwang said here today that the prevention of crimes by police
at the grassroots levels is the key factor to safeguarding social
stability.
</P>
<P>
Police at the substations have the closest ties with the local
residents and are acquainted with the areas under their
jurisdiction, so they should act as a major force maintaining law
and order in localities, Jia said.
</P>
<P>
The minister of public security made the remarks at a national
conference on the work of police substations, which is being held
in this capital of northeast China's Jilin Province.
</P>
<P>
He commended the work of establishing safety neighborhood
communities in Fuzhou, the capital city of east China's fujian
Province, where the occurrence rate of criminal cases had dropped
by 46 percent in 1997 over the previous year, and cases regarding
burglaring, looting and stealing of bicycles and motor vehicles
reduced by some 50 percent.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he called on grassroots police to further reinforce
ties with the masses of people and serve them wholeheartedly, so
as to win their trust and support the fight against crime.
</P>
</TEXT>
