<HEADLINE> Mongolia Eyes New Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Mongolia is trying to improve
its investment environment in order to attract more foreign
investment and revitalize its economy, Prime Minister Tsakhya
Elbegdorj said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Investment procedures will be simplified and investment laws
will be improved to encourage more foreign investment in the
inland Asian nation, Elbegdorj said in an interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Placing the infrastructure sector as the top priority on the
investment agenda, the official called for more foreign investment
in transportation, energy, post and communication sectors.
</P>
<P>
Mongolia will host an international investment consultative
conference on June 24-26 to help channel foreign investment into
the sectors of farming, animal husbandry, light industry and
tourism.
</P>
<P>
On Sino-Mongolian cooperation, Elbegdorj said Mongolia attaches
importance to economic cooperation with China and foresees
promising prospects for future development of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Anticipating a great potential in goods imports and technology
transfers from China, Elbegdorj said conditions will improve for
expanded economic cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
