<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Chief Executive on Visit to Australia, New Zealand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region of China left here
Saturday night on a six-day visit to Australia and New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
Tung is scheduled to tour Sydney, Melbourne, Auckland and
Wellington to strengthen Hong Kong's ties with the two countries
and to update political and business leaders in both countries on
the latest developments in the SAR.
</P>
<P>
An SAR spokesman said earlier that Tung will reassure overseas
audiences of Hong Kong's continued role as a regional business and
financial center and as the preeminent gateway to China's mainland
and the East Asian region.
</P>
<P>
The chief executive will exchange views with leaders of both
countries on the need for further trade liberalization through
multilateral efforts before the turn of the century as well as on
other issues such as travel arrangements for HKSAR passport
holders and the impact of the Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters before departure, Tung expressed the hope
that the Japanese yen would be stabilized as soon as possible.
</P>
</TEXT>
