<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Injured McCarthy Misses Denmark Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 13 (Xinhua) -- An embattled South Africa
suffered another big blow to their World Cup aspirations as their
star striker Benedict McCarthy is out for the crucial Group C
match against Denmark in Toulouse on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
McCarthy, who was stretchered off late in the match against
France on Friday night, suffered serious damage to his left ankle
ligaments and would be out for the match against the Danes, South
African Press Association quoted team doctor Victor Ramathesele as
saying on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
McCarthy, 20, was involved in a rather innocuous tackle with a
French player in the 87th minute of the match against France,
which ended in a 0:3 defeat for the South Africans.
</P>
<P>
The young Ajax Amsterdam player did not make much impact on the
heart of the French defense, who bottled him up with single-minded
determination.
</P>
<P>
There was also concern over fellow striker Phil Masinga, who
took a knock on the shin during the game but bravely continued for
the full 90 minutes, the report said.
</P>
<P>
"Masinga's injury looks more serious than we thought, and I am
sending him for X-rays for a second opinion to be absolutely sure
of the severity of his injury," Ramathesele said on the team's
arrival at Vichy.
</P>
<P>
South Africa must win both their remaining matches, against
Denmark and Saudi Arabia, to advance to the next round.
</P>
<P>
Coach Philippe Troussier, pleased with his team's performance
in the Friday match but not happy with the margin of defeat, said
the side would start their preparations for the Denmark encounter
with a practice on Saturday evening. 
</P>
</TEXT>
