<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Army Chief Stresses Need for Upgrading Readiness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Army chief said
Saturday that "very responsible, mature and foolproof policies at
the national level will continue to be enforced to control, direct
and manage further developments in the nuclear field."
</P>
<P>
Chief of Army Staff General Jehangir Karamat made the remarks
while addressing officers during his day-long visit to two
garrisons in northeast Punjab Province, according to a press
release by Inter Services Public Relations Directorate.
</P>
<P>
General Karamat stressed the need to enhance combat efficiency
and upgrade operational readiness for all possible contingencies,
especially low-intensity conflicts and internal security
situations.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the recent nuclear tests, General Karamat said
that Pakistan had reacted in the interest of national security and
that the strategic imbalance in the region had to be redressed.
</P>
<P>
He said the testing was Pakistan's own effort and success had
been achieved at great costs. "Therefore, very responsible,
foolproof policies at the national level would continue to be
enforced to control, direct and manage further developments in
this field," he added.
</P>
<P>
Responding to a question, he said national security depends on
many other factors besides military and nuclear capabilities and
among them economic resilience and internal stability are the most
important, Karamat said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
