<HEADLINE> 10 Killed in Traffic Accident in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 13 (Xinhua) -- At least 10 people were killed and
many others injured on Saturday in a traffic accident in
Eskisehir province near Ankara, capital of Turkey, the
semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred when a tanker carrying liquid gas collided
with a passenger bus from the Kutahya Tourism Company on the
Bozuyuk-Inonu Highway in Eskisehir, the report said.
</P>
<P>
A fire brigade team rushed to the scene and tried to put out
the flame caused by the collision. The highway has been closed as
the rescue work was going on. 
</P>
</TEXT>
