<HEADLINE> Nigeria Beat Spain in Group of Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
NANTES, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Olympic champions Nigeria overcame a
slow start to beat Spain 3-2 in an exciting match at the "Group of
Death" here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Spainish team opened the scoring at the 21st minute through
a free-kick. But three minutes later the Nigerian team levelled the
score 1-1 as Mutiu Adepoju.
</P>
<P>
In the second half, the Nigerian team played much better though
they were again one goal behind at the 47th minute as Raul sent home
a right-footer.
</P>
<P>
Garba Lawal dribbled down the left flank and centered, the
Spanish goal-keeper Andoni Zubizarreta tried to clear the ball only
to touch the ball into the net at the 73rd minute.
</P>
<P>
Four minutes later, Sunday Oliseh fired a fierce long shot out of
the penalty to be Zubizarreta again and put the Nigerian team 3-2
ahead.
</P>
<P>
In the remaining minutes of the match, the Spanish team tried
hard for an equaliser. But the experienced Nigerian team didn't
give them any more chances.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria led the group with three points, followed by Bulgaria
and Paraguay with one point each. The two teams played to a
goalless draw on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
