<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Increase Bus Fares </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Government-owned Zimbabwe United
Passenger Company (ZUPCO) is to increase its fares by between
seven and 16 percent with effect from Monday or June 15.
</P>
<P>
ZUPCO Public Relations Manager Ben Mauchaza Saturday told the
Zimbabwe News Agency that the increases had been necessitated by
a number of factors which included the rise in prices of major
inputs such as tyres and lubricants.
</P>
<P>
The prices of all imported vehicle spare parts had gone up by
81 percent mainly because of the devaluation of the Zimbabwean
Dollar last year while tyre costs had gone up by a minimum of
28.3 percent and lubricants by up to 80 percent, he said.
</P>
<P>
The increase in fares had become unavoidable but the company
would ensure that fares were kept at a minimum level, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
