<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Enterprises Expand Markets in Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, June 13 (Xinhua) -- More and more enterprises from the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) are showing great
interest in expanding trade relations with northeast China, an
official from the Hong Kong Trade Development Council said here
today.
</P>
<P>
The council has organized many businesses in the Hong Kong SAR
to attend the upcoming Ninth Harbin Economic and Trade
Negotiations Fair, said Song Ying, chief representative in charge
of the council's business in northeast China.
</P>
<P>
China's northernmost province of Heilongjiang, which does a
flourishing border trade with members of the Commonwealth of
Independent States (CIS), is particularly attractive to Hong Kong
business people.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong business people regard the fair in Harbin, capital
of Heilongjiang, as the best channel for entering the regional
market," Song said.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong enterprises signed about 4.1 million US dollars-worth
of orders with local partners at last year's Harbin fair.
</P>
<P>
The 15-odd enterprises from Hong Kong which attend the fair will
display various commodities, including garments, jewelry, cosmetics,
electronic goods and traditional Chinese medicines, Song said.
</P>
<P>
Business people from Australia, Hungary, Japan, the Republic of
Korea (ROK), Russia, Sweden, Switzerland, Yugoslavia and other
countries and regions will also attend the seven-day fair
beginning June 15. 
</P>
</TEXT>
