<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hun Sen Welcomes Defection of Five Khmer Rouge Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia's Second Prime
Minister Hun Sen welcomed the return of five high-ranking Khmer
Rouge (KR) officials to the Royal Cambodian government.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia's state television Saturday evening released a letter
sent by Hun Sen to Chan Youran and four other KR officials who
defected from the Khmer Rouge.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen, on behalf of the Cambodian government and joint
commander-in-chief of the Cambodian Royal Army, said he would like
to give them a warm welcome on their return to the big family --
the kingdom of Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
Chan Youran, Mak Ben, En Sopheap, Kor Bum and Thiounn Thioeun,
the five senior officials of the so-called KR government, signed a
statement on Friday announcing they had split from the Khmer
Rouge's hardliners Ta Mok and Nuon Chea.
</P>
<P>
A large number of KR guerrillas also defected to the government
following the death of Pol Pot on April 15, and in response to the
government's continuing efforts to eliminate the remaining KR
rebels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
