<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Museveni Calls National Conference of Ruling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni
has announced that the first meeting of the national conference,
the highest organ under the ruling National Resistance Movement,
will take place on July 12.
</P>
<P>
A press release from the president office said Friday that the
conference will be held in the international conference center.
</P>
<P>
During the conference, the chairperson and vice chairperson of
the national conference and National Political Commissar (NPC)
will be elected.
</P>
<P>
A Monitor report Saturday predicted that Museveni will be
elected to steer the national conference.
</P>
<P>
Under the Movement Act, the chairperson of the national
conference shall submit to the national executive committee a
list of no more than three candidates for the office of NPC.
</P>
<P>
It is alleged that a crevice has been created in the movement.
The young parliamentarians have a list of their candidates for
this post while the president's preference falls on different
people.
</P>
<P>
The national conference meets every two years though it can
hold extraordinary meetings when necessary. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
