<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambicans Urged to Participate in Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, June 13 (Xinhua) -- The ruling Mozambique Liberation
Front (Frelimo) Saturday appealed to Mozambicans to participate
actively in the forthcoming local elections scheduled for June
30.
</P>
<P>
Frelimo made the call in a message to the country to mark the
23rd anniversary of Mozambique's independence, won on June 25,
1975.
</P>
<P>
The participation of all voters in the elections is of great
significance to the success of the election, said Frelimo, adding
it is also conducive to the consolidation of democracy in the
country as well as to the expansion of regional autonomy to the
whole Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
Frelimo also called on all citizens to safeguard the national
unity in a bid to build a united and powerful nation.
</P>
<P>
With the election drawing near, accusations from the country's
largest opposition -- The National Resistance of Mozambique --
were also on the rise to sabotage and obstruct the elections.
Reports said a total of 17 opposition parties have stated that
they would not take part in the local elections to be held in 33
cities and towns. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
