<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPPCC Chairman Meets Former French PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), met with former French Prime Minister Alain
Juppe, who is now mayor of Bordeaux, here today.
</P>
<P>
Li recalled his recent visit to France, saying that he has
become deeply aware through the visit that China and France have
many reasons to enhance their co-operation and exchanges.
</P>
<P>
He noted that both countries, which have a longstanding history
and splendid cultures, are currently engaged in developing economy
and upgrading people's living standards, and they have identical
or similar views on many international issues.
</P>
<P>
Sino-French relations should be advanced on the existing basis
since this is not only in the interest of the people of the two
countries, but is beneficial to the world peace and stability, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Li expressed appreciations over the forging of sisterly-city
ties between Bordeaux and Wuhan, a transportation hub and an
industrial center in central China.
</P>
<P>
Co-operation between the cities of the two countries constitute
an important part of the overall friendship, he said, expressing
the hope the two cities would learn from each other so as to boost
their own development and to contribute to the progress of
bilateral relations as well.
</P>
<P>
Juppe said France has always considered China its major
co-operative partner, and that just as China, France opposes
hegemonism. He expressed satisfaction with bilateral co-operation
in some current world issues, and appreciated the positive role
China has been playing in helping stablize the Asian economic
situation.
</P>
<P>
Juppe is visiting China at the invitation of the Chinese
People's Association for Friendship with Foregin Countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
