<HEADLINE> Work Starts on Key Railway Line in Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the northern
section of a trunk rail line in southwest China, a state-listed
key project for the Ninth Five-Year Plan period (1996-2000),
started at Yibin City in Sichuan Province yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The line will connect Neijiang City in Sichuan with Kunming,
capital of southwestern Yunnan Province, with a total length of
854 km.
</P>
<P>
The project, one of the nine new railway projects for this
year, is expected to be completed in the year 2002, at an
estimated cost of 11.6 billion yuan (1.4 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Construction of the line's middle and southern sections will be
started in mid-June and the latter half of June, respectively, a
project official said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
