<DOCNO> XIE19980613.0070 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CAS to Head Knowledge Innovation Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 13 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Sciences
(CAS), China's top scientific research body, announced here today
that it is to take the lead in the country in the implementation of the
national Knowledge Innovation Program.
</P>
<P>
Chen Yiyu, CAS vice-president, said the creation of the
national knowledge innovation system is the only choice for China
to meet the challenge of the 21st century, when the
knowledge-based part of the economy will take the dominant
position.
</P>
<P>
He said the CAS in the next few years will focus on strategic
basic research, technology for keeping sustainable development,
high-tech innovation for civilian use and leading-edge natural
science.
</P>
<P>
Chen added that high-yield crop seed breeding, human genetic
resources and their applications, and new pharmaceuticals for the
treatment of major diseases will be covered in the basic research
programs.
</P>
<P>
He said the CAS will also launch research into the sustainable
development of the Yangtze and Yellow River basins, ecology and
biological resources.
</P>
<P>
The CAS vice-president said that high-tech innovation research
will focus on information and telecommunications technology,
genetic and protein engineering and other new scientific fields.
</P>
<P>
He announced that by the year 2010 the CAS will become the
country's national natural science and high-tech innovation center
focussing on strategies for national economic and social
development.
</P>
<P>
To achieve its goals, the CAS is to carry out structural reform
by cutting the number of permanent scientists from the current
68,000 to around 30,000 by 2010, while increasing the number of
visiting researchers and scholars from 15,000 to some 30,000.
</P>
<P>
The CAS will also build eight research bases in Beijing,
Shanghai, Lanzhou, Kunming and Shenyang, he revealed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
