<HEADLINE> ``Improved Legal System Guarantee for Sustained Development" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Cheng Siyuan, vice-chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC), said
in this capital city of Shandong Province today that the
improvement of China's legal system will serve as a guarantee for
environmental protection and sustained development.
</P>
<P>
A national legal system for the protection of the environment and
resources will be set up in coming five years, Cheng said during
an eight-day inspection tour on ocean environmental protection
organized by the NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
He urged people's congresses at the provincial level to work
out their own regulations in light of local conditions.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, people's congresses at all levels should enhance
their supervision of the implementation of the laws on
environmental protection and correct the tendency for laws not to
be enforced strictly and violations of laws not to be
investigated, he said.
</P>
<P>
The vice-chairman called on all provinces to launch mass
campaigns on disseminating elementary knowledge of the law.
</P>
<P>
Shandong has a coastline of 3,121 km, accounting for one sixth
of the national total. Its marine economic sector yielded an
output value of 60 billion yuan in 1997.
</P>
<P>
However, the quality of Shandong's offshore water has
deteriorated in recent years owing to the discharge of untreated
industrial waste water, the vice-chairman noted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
