<HEADLINE> Concerts Honor Famous Chinese Musician </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 13 (Xinhua) -- A symphony concert was given in
this capital of Guangdong Province today at the newly completed
Xinghai Concert Hall, to mark the 93rd birth anniversary of Xian
Xinghai, a famous Chinese musician.
</P>
<P>
Musicians from Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou, Hong Kong and
Macao participated in the performance, which is the first of nine
concerts to be given in the coming two weeks at the Xinghai
Concert Hall.
</P>
<P>
Completed earlier this year with a total investment of 250
million yuan (about 30 million US dollars), the Xinghai
Concert Hall is named after Xian, whose ancestral home is
in Guangdong.
</P>
<P>
The concerts will include Chinese folk songs, concertos played
on traditional Chinese musical instruments and compositions by
Beethoven and other world-renowned musicians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
