<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets Former French Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji met
with former French Prime Minister Alain Juppe here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Extending his welcome to Juppe, who is now mayor of Bordeaux,
Zhu briefed him on China's economic situation.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that China attaches importance to the development of
its friendly relations with France and the European Union, and
hopes to strengthen cooperation with them, so as to contribute to
world peace, stability and development.
</P>
<P>
President of the Chinese People's Association for Friendship
with Foreign Countries Qi Huaiyuan and its Vice-President Chen
Haosu were present at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Juppe arrived here this morning and is scheduled to leave
for Wuhan, capital of central China's Hubei Province, to sign an
agreement on the establishment of friendly relations between
Bordeaux and Wuhan. 
</P>
