<HEADLINE> International Anti-Drug Day Marked in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 13 (Xinhua) -- A show was staged here Saturday
to mark the UN International Day Against Drug Abuse and Illicit
Trafficking.
</P>
<P>
The 90-minute show, featuring anti-drug messages, songs and
music, was organized by the Narcotics Division of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
During the show held at a local shopping center, performers
entertained the audience with songs, and teamed up with the
audience in a quiz and games to popularize anti-drug messages.
</P>
<P>
The show was accompanied by an anti-drug photo exhibition and
display of fake drugs.
</P>
<P>
According to a local official, the number of reported drug
abusers dropped to 17,555 in Hong Kong in 1997, a 10.9 percent
decrease compared with that of 1996 as a result of strenuous
efforts made by the SAR government.
</P>
<P>
Apart from education and publicity, the SAR government
increased in 1997 the penalties for exploiting young people in
drug trafficking and tightened up control on certain chemicals to
prevent them from being used in manufacturing of drugs.
</P>
<P>
The government also continued maintaining close liaison with
various countries and international organizations in combating
drug trafficking and money laundering. 
</P>
</TEXT>
