<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Conduct National Census in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 13 (Xinhua)-- A national census will be conducted
in Vietnam on next April 1, according to a latest decision by
Vietnam's Prime Minister Phan Van Khai.
</P>
<P>
An official report said Saturday the census will focus on the
scale and trend of internal migration, education levels of the
population, employment situation, birth rate, mortality rate and
population growth rate.
</P>
<P>
The census will for the first time collect data on the housing
and living standards in the country.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that some 300,000 workers will be needed to
conduct the census, with 2,500 at provincial and district levels
and 250,000 at grassroot levels.
</P>
<P>
The preliminary results of the census are scheduled to be made
public in June, 1999, and the complete results, in May, 2000.
</P>
