<HEADLINE> China Develops Large Bearing for Power Stations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists at the Harbin
Electric Machinery Corporation have developed a bearing that can
take a load of 6,000 tons, for use on generators.
</P>
<P>
It was developed with technology from Switzerland's ABB company.
</P>
<P>
The Harbin company has cooperated with ABB in building eight
generators for the Three Gorges Project, the world's largest water
conservation project.
</P>
<P>
Qu Dazhuang, head of the company's research institute, says
that previously the biggest bearing of this kind was a 4,700
tonnage thrust bearing.
</P>
<P>
The thrust bearing has to withstand the total weight of a
hydroelectric power generator and is essential for its safe
operation for a long period of time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
