<HEADLINE> Vietnam Launches Campaign to Protect Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam has launched a campaign to
protect children from abuse, Vietnam News Agency reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Mass organizations and a large number of newspapers, radios and
TV stations will participate in the campaign.
</P>
<P>
The organizers of the campaign hope to raise people's awareness
of child protection and care.
</P>
<P>
A survey conducted in 1997 showed there are more than 12,200
street children in the country, 40 percent of them under 14.
</P>
<P>
The majority of these children are illiterate and suffer from
illnesses.
</P>
<P>
Forty percent of them earn their food by polishing shoes and
the remainder sell newspapers or work as domestic servants for a
living.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, 15 percent of the total 7,000 prostitutes in the
countries are under 16 years old. 
