<HEADLINE> World Cup hke -- Marseille Fans Celebrate after French Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MARSEILLE, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of French fans took to the
streets here Friday night to celebrate the hosts' victory in the
opening game as the country returned to the World Cup finals after 12
years of absence.
</P>
<P>
"It was the Marseille players who won the game," cried a fan waving
a French tricolor flag on a street near the Stade Velodrome.
</P>
<P>
He was amid the cheering crowds that celebrated with cars' horn
blaring and flag waving from a train of cars in this soccer-mad city.
</P>
<P>
Fans here were apparently pleased by the fact that two of three
goals in the 3-0 win over South Africa were scored by players from the
local Olympique Marseille club.
</P>
<P>
Marseille striker Christophe Duggarry put the French on the
scoreboard with a header on a first-half corner kick delivered by
playmaker Zinedine Zidane, who also was raised by the Algerian parents
in the city.
</P>
<P>
Ironically, South African defender Pierra Issa, who scored an own
goal in the second half, also plays for Olympique Marseille in the
French league.
</P>
<P>
France will face Saudi Arabia, the 1-0 losers to Denmark in an
earlier Group C match, in the Stade de France in St. Denis on June 18.
</P>
