<HEADLINE> Compulsory Education Project in Southwestern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, June 13 (Xinhua) -- The State Compulsory Education
Project for Poverty-stricken Regions has begun in China's Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region, the local government reports.
</P>
<P>
The central government will allocate 315 million yuan in
special funds over the next three years for the project, the
biggest nationwide education program in Chinese history, for the
autonomous region's 50 impoverished counties.
</P>
<P>
The local government will support the undertaking with 575
million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The funds will mainly be spent on 3,478 new primary schools
with a total area of 1.37 million square meters. In addition,
120,200 square meters of school buildings will be renovated or
enlarged over the next three years.
</P>
<P>
The money will also be used for books, teaching materials, and
training programs for teachers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
