<DOCNO> XIE19980613.0115 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam and Slovakia Sign Debt Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam and Slovakia signed here an
agreement to settle Vietnam's debts, Vietnam News Agency (VNA)
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The document was signed by Vietnamese Finance Minister Nguyen
Sinh Hung and State Secretary at the Finance Ministry of the
Slovak Republic Tatiana Silhankova.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, all the debts that Vietnam owed to
Slovakia in convertible rouble will be exchanged for the
U.S. dollar at mutually acceptable rate, and payment of settled
debts will be made in goods.
</P>
<P>
The deal aims to help Vietnam pay its debts to Slovakia and to
deepen the cooperation for development and the commercial ties
between the governments, finance ministries and business people of
the two countries, Silhankova said.
</P>
<P>
Hung and Silhankova will explore the signing of an agreement on
avoiding double taxation, an agreement on investment promotion and
protection between the two countries and an accord on financial
cooperation between the two countries' finance ministries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
