<HEADLINE> Chinese Develop New Ejection Seat To Increase Pilot Safety </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Flight safety engineers of the
Chinese air force have invented a new device that can eject pilots
from an aircraft at zero speed, zero altitude that could save more
lives.
</P>
<P>
Military sources say that the device takes three-tenths of a
second at the most to kick in when an aircraft is in trouble at a
speed of zero to 250 kilometers per hour.
</P>
<P>
The device has proven itself effective and reliable in more
than 140 field trials, with a 100 percent success rate. 
