<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenya Transit Point for Asia Drug Trafficking: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Kenya is a transit point for
narcotic drugs from mainly the Asian sub-continent, Kenyan
Cabinet Minister in the Office of the President Marsden Madoka
has said.
</P>
<P>
Drug problems in the east African country are no different
from that of some main narcotic consuming countries, he was
quoted Saturday by the East African Standard newspaper as saying.
</P>
<P>
Madoka termed Kenya's geographical position as strategic for
drug source countries, adding that the state's effective
communications network only serve to make it the ideal conduit
for international drug runners.
</P>
<P>
However, Kenya, a supporter of the African Common Position on
Drug Control, has taken measures to cope with escalating drug
related problems at the national level, he said at the 20th
special session of the U.N. General Assembly in New York.
</P>
<P>
The country has already established an Anti-Narcotics Unit as
well as a permanent inter-ministerial drug coordinating committee
to harmonize, monitor and evaluate all drug control measures
nationwide, he said.
</P>
<P>
Establishing a national crime research center last year and
enacting the narcotic drugs and psychotrophic substances control
act in 1994 were also among the measures.
</P>
<P>
The act incorporates various provisions of the U.N.
conventions on narcotic drugs and psychotrophic substances.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Kenya is working on the ratification of the
convention on Psychotrophic substances of 1971, which would
compliment the already ratified single Convention on Narcotic
Drugs of 1961, and the Convention against Illicit Traffic in
Narcotic Drugs and Psychotrophic substances of 1988.
</P>
<P>
Madoka added that Kenya, Uganda and Tanzania have drawn up a
protocol in common efforts to combat drug trafficking in the east
African region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980613.0122 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-13 </DATE_TIME>
