<HEADLINE> Top Seed Knocked out in U.S. Badminton Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Taipei's Fung Permadi
defeated top seed Ardy Wiranata of the United States 10-15, 15-8,
15-7 to reach the men's final of the U.S. Badminton Open
Tournament in Orange, California on Friday evening.
</P>
<P>
Permadi, ranked 31st in the world, will play Scotland's Bruce
Flockhart in Saturday's final after Flockhart Beating
second-seeded American Kevin Han 15-10, 15-7 in the other
semi-final.
</P>
<P>
The 15th-ranked Wiranata, a silver medalist in the 1992
Olympics for Indonesia, was playing his first tournament for the
U.S. team, which he now coaches.
</P>
<P>
Ye Ping Tang of the United States and Scotland's Elinor
Middlemiss will play for two finals on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
They will meet each other in mixed doubles, where Tang will
team with Andy Chong against Middlemiss and her husband, Kenny,
the second-seeded pair.
</P>
<P>
Tang will also play second-seeded Briton Jo Muggeridge in the
women's singles final, while Middlemiss will join Kirsteen McEwan
as the top-seeded team in women's doubles final against Robbyn
Hermitage and Milaine Cloutier of Canada.
</P>
<P>
In men's doubles final, Chinese Taipei's Shin-Jeng Horng and
Wei-Jen Lee will take on second seed Canadians Iain Sydie and
Darryl Jung. 
</P>
</TEXT>
