<HEADLINE> Jazz Edges Bulls to Win NBA Finals Game 5 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Karl Malone hit 17 of 27 shots
from the field and scored 39 points to help the Utah Jazz edge the
Chicago Bulls 83-81 in NBA Game 5, narrowing the series gap to 2-3
Friday night.
</P>
<P>
Antoine Carr hit three vital baskets of his 12 points in the
final stage to smash the Bulls's hope of landing the sixth
championship tonight.
</P>
<P>
The next two games will go to Jazz's home court with Game 6
starting Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Toni Kukoc scored 30 points, including a big three with 5.5
seconds to go, his effort put the Bulls 81-82 behind the Jazz, but
with another point from Utah in the final second, the Bulls failed
to create a miracle to turn the table.
</P>
<P>
Michael Jordan added 28 points for the Bulls, but Scottie
Pippen failed to rise on the crucial occasion, only making six
points from his 2-of-16 shots.
</P>
<P>
Malone finished with a series-high points, 17 in the third
quarter. "We just want to win one game at a time. It's not a
victory of myself, the teamwork is always very important. We have
got a good chance now. I am happy to bring the series back to our
home floor," Malone said after the triumph.
</P>
<P>
The Jazz were dragging 36-30 at halftime after Malone elbowed
Dennis Rodman to draw a techinical foul.
</P>
<P>
But Malone nailed the first three shots of the third quarter to
help the Jazz turn the tide for the first time before winding up
the period 59-55.
</P>
<P>
When the Jazz surged ahead, they never looked back and kept a
small margin deep into the final quarter.
</P>
<P>
If Utah win Game 6, a decisive seventh game would be played
there next Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
