<HEADLINE> Colombo Takes Measures Agaisnt Spread of Cholera </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 13 (Xinhua) -- The Colombo municipal Council
(CMC) has taken measures to prevent the spreading of cholera in
the city after four cholera positive cases were reported there,
CMC sources said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Although cholera cases have been reported from different parts
of the country, the capital city has been free from cholera for
the last six months due to strict measures and constant
surveillance carried out by the CMC, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
From January 1 to June 10 this year, over 300 cholera cases had
been reported from all parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
The CMC has taken immediate measures by disinfecting the toilets
and drains in the affected areas of the city, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Water is tested daily from inlets and outlets of these
reservoirs and chlorine is added before distribution.
</P>
<P>
Health education programs throughout the city are being
launched while special programs are being given to school students
to educate them about cholera, the sources added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
