<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine and the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO) held their first defense ministerial meeting
Friday at NATO's headquarters in Brussels.
</P>
<P>
Ivan Bizhan, the Ukrainian first deputy defense minister, and
Javier Solana, secretary general of NATO, attended the meeting,
the Press Bureau of the Foreign Ministry of Ukraine said.
</P>
<P>
A regular meeting between Ukrainian and NATO defense ministers
will play an important role in developing the special partnership
between the two sides as well as safeguarding the world security,
Bizhan said.
</P>
<P>
He said that he hopes the NATO will be able to turn the Yavorov
Training Range into an international military training base to
train soldiers from Ukraine and the NATO.
</P>
<P>
Solana praised the work done by the joint team for Ukrainian
military reform, which was set up recently under a NATO framework.
</P>
<P>
He said a new step toward a closer relation would be the
establishment of the NATO representative office in Kiev, capital
of Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
Both sides agreed to strengthen defense and military
cooperation under the framework of NATO's Partnership for Peace
program designed for military cooperation with Non-NATO countries
in central and eastern Europe. 
