<HEADLINE> Indonesia Freezes Tourism Promotion Offices Abroad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 13 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian Government will
temporarily freeze tourism promotion offices in seven countries
because of financial constraints, Antara News Agency Saturday
quoted a senior tourism official as saying.
</P>
<P>
After consultations with his aides, Minister of Tourism, Arts
and Culture Marzuki Usman had agreed to freeze the activities of
these offices for at least one year.
</P>
<P>
These tourism promotion offices are located in Frankfurt,
Tokyo, Hong Kong, Singapore, Los Angeles, London and Melbourne.
</P>
<P>
"The decision to call our tourism representatives home was
taken after considering the rupiah's continuing slide against the
U.S. dollar," said Andi Mappisameng, Director General of Tourism.
</P>
<P>
Funds earmarked to finance the operations of the offices were
based on an exchange rate of 5,000 rupiah per U.S. dollar, but in
the latest money market developments the dollar unexpectedly rose
three times the pegged rate of 5,000 rupiah, Andi said.
</P>
<P>
Andi said earlier this month that it is practically impossible
for the country's tourism sector to record any growth this year
because of the ongoing monetary crisis. The sector managed to
bring in foreign exchange of no less than 6.6 billion U.S. dollars
last year.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the government is planning to establish a
Trade Tourism and Investment agency to handle tourism promotion
abroad. The agency would be staffed with personnel from the Trade
and Industry Ministry, the Investment Ministry and the Tourism,
Arts and Culture Ministry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
