</P>
<P>
LONDON -- Foreign ministers from the Group of Eight (G8)
countries Friday decided to postpone most international financial
institutions' loans to India and Pakistan for their undertaking a
series of nuclear tests despite strong international opposition.
</P>
<P>
Foreign ministers from the the United States, Russia, Japan,
Germany, France, Britain, Italy and Canada agreed in a final
communique that they would work to delay most international loans
to the two countries. (UK-G8 Meeting)
</P>
<P>
