</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. space shuttle Discovery landed Friday on
time at 2 p.m. in Kennedy Space Center, Florida, concluding NASA's
final docking with the Russian Mir Station and bringing back the
last American astronaut Andrew Thomas.
</P>
<P>
Alpha Magnetic Spectrometer, a high energy particle detector
designed and manufactured by scientists from China, the United
States and other countries, also was back on Earth.
(US-Space-Shuttle-Landing) 
