won the Silver Bear in the Berlin Festival this year, has won a
new international award, the Huesca, in Spain a Short Length
Feature Festival.
</P>
<P>
The 10-minute film depicts the life of the inhabitants who live
in the ruins of a cinema theater in Old Managua.
</P>
<P>
CARACAS -- A cycle of cultural activities starts this Sunday
commemorating the 100th birthday of Spanish poet Federico Garcia
Lorca.
</P>
<P>
Lorca, who died during the Civil War, is considered one of the
few creative masters of this century, the owner of a magical,
multiple talent.
</P>
<P>
SANTIAGO -- While famous Chilean football forward Marcelo Salas
made his brilliant debut in France against Italy, scoring two
goals in the World Cup, the book "Salas, the History of a Matador,"
hit the bookstore shelves and the newspaper stands.
</P>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA -- An exhibition to mark the centennial of
the great Spanish poet and playwright, Federico Garcia Lorca, will
open on June 10-August 14.
</P>
<P>
The display takes a tour of Lorca's life with photographs,
drawings, posters, books and magazines that recreate the most
important moments of the poet. 
</P>
