<DOCNO> XIE19980613.0179 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arafat Warns of Danger of Peace Collapse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat
Friday warned the world of the dire consequences of a collapse of
the peace negotiations with Israel.
</P>
<P>
"I have warned before, and I warn now, before it is too late,
that a collapse of the peace process will plunge the whole region
into a cycle of violence, conflict and total, unlimited
instability," Arafat told a dinner hosted in his honor by Arab
ambassadors and the Italy-Arab Chamber of Commerce, in Rome.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian leader is in Italy for a two-day visit. He
urged Italy and its EU partners to pursue moves complementary to
those of the United States to get the peace process moving.
</P>
<P>
According to Arafat, the Israelis have not only frozen all
previous agreements, but have also promoted a "vast movement of
settlement" in the occupied eastern part of Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
He insisted, however, that peace in the Middle East is in
conformity with the interests of the whole international
community, despite existing difficulties.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Romano Prodi met Arafat earlier in the
day. Prodi expressed hope that Israel and Palestine can overcome
the present severe difficulties through negotiations.
</P>
<P>
A communique from Prodi's office said Italy believes the
willingness to support the peace process should be used "as widely
as possible."
</P>
<P>
It also affirmed Italy's willingness to propose joint European
Union-United States moves to EU nations when "opportune and
necessary." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
