<HEADLINE> U.S. Soccer Coach Criticizes Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Three days before his team's
World Cup opener, U.S. coach Steve Sampson criticized german head
coach Bertu Vigts for not respecting the Americans.
</P>
<P>
"Bertu Vigts walked out 20 minutes before the end of the
Belgium match, that shows a lack of respect for the United States
team," Sampson said in Paris, a press report said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
"In Europe, they have no respect for the U.S. team. Frankly, we
haven't earned it," he added.
</P>
<P>
Sampson, who was referring to the Americans' 2-0 loss at
Brussels on February 25, is openly using the respect issue to
motivate his players going into Monday's game againt Germany in
Paris.
</P>
<P>
The United States has a 10-29-5 record in Europe against
European opponents and has been outscored by 123-42. In their last
10 matches, the Americans did pretty good, beating Iceland 1-0 and
Austria 3-0. 
</P>
