</P>
<P>
-- Japan's gross domestic product (GDP) for fiscal 1997 dropped
by an inflation-adjusted 0.7 percent from a year earlier, the
first decline in 23 years and the largest year-on-year fall since
the end of World War II.
</P>
<P>
