<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Cup hke -- France Open Campaign with 3-0 Win </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MARSEILLE, June 12 (Xinhua) -- France returned to the World Cup
finals after 12 years' absence with an overwhelming 3-0 win over South
Africa in their Group C opener here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
France had all guns firing from the beginning in this game at this
soccer-mad city and Christophe Duggary found the net with a header in
the 35th minute on a corner kick delivered by Zinedine Zidane.
</P>
<P>
There was no let-up in the second half for the French attackers,
with Inter Milan star Youri Djorkaeff chipping a ball toward South
African keeper Hans Vonk in the 78th minute.
</P>
<P>
Vonk made the correct judgement and did a slide-dive toward the
ball's path. But South African defender Pierre Issa, in an attempt to
stop the ball before the keeper, bounced the ball up over Vonk into
the net with his leg.
</P>
<P>
Thierry Henry, with European Cup semifinalist club Monaco, sealed
the victory for the hosts by netting in close range at the dying
minutes of the game after beating three South African players.
</P>
<P>
Zidane said after the game that the victory proved that the
pre-game critism against the team was all wrong.
</P>
<P>
"This victory is the effort of the whole team," said Zidane. "There
has been a lot of critism concerning our performances in the
friendlies but the friendlies could not prove anything.
</P>
<P>
"It's same for my teammate Duggary. You can see he performed well
tonight," he added.
</P>
<P>
French coach Aime Jacquet had been blasted for picking the
Olympique Marseille striker, who had previously a low scoring ratio at
international level.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
