<HEADLINE> World Cup hke -- Denmark Beats Saudi Arabia 1-0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LENS, France, June 12 (Xinhua) -- A second-half header from Marc
Rieper gave former European champion Denmark a 1-0 win over Saudi
Arabia 1-0 in a Group C match at the soccer World Cup finals here on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Rieper, the robust defender who transferred to Scottish club Celtic
from England's West Ham United for 1.5 million pounds last year,
scored in the 69th minute in the second half.
</P>
<P>
The 30-year-old veteran, coming into the match with the experience
from 52 international caps, headed the ball home over the reaching
arms of Mohammed Al-Deayea.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia then beefed up the offences but Denmark, featuring a
solid defence and star goalkeeper Peter Schmeichel, held out the game.
</P>
<P>
After the whistle the 34-year-old Manchester United keeper waved to
the vocal Dannish fans among 38, 140 spectators at the Stade Felix
Bollaert.
</P>
<P>
Rieper and his teammates Morten Wieghorst and Allan Nielsen were
cautioned in the game with yellow cards by referee Javier Alberto
Castrilli.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia's Khalid Al Muwald was also warned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
