<HEADLINE> world cup hke -- Bulgarian Coach Disappointed About Draw </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MONTPELLIER, June 12 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian coach Hristo Bonev
said he was very disappointed about the draw with Paraguay.
</P>
<P>
"We're very disappointed not to have won because we were better
than Paraguay. In the first half were in a good position to score.
We had lots of chances but we just couldn't pull it off." said Bonev.
</P>
<P>
Bonev blamed the refree of the match:"Maybe the penalty that the
refree didn't blow at the beginning of the match could have changed
the outcome. But I still think we played very well."
</P>
<P>
The Paraguay coach Paulo Cesar Carpeggiani was also not
satisfied with the result:"We think it's an unfair result--we had a
lot of chances. We should have made full use of the advantage we
had over the Bulgarians."
</P>
<P>
Paraguay's star goal-keeper Jose Luis Chilavert Gonzalez said
after the match:"We feel really at home in Montpellie. That should
have helped us to win. We played well and I'm quite happy. I'm
proud of our quality of play."
</P>
<P>
Midfielder Roberto Acuna of Paraguay blamed their draw with
Bulgaria for poor finishing:"We were not able to score. We're going
to try to win the next match and not lose our calm for the rest of
the competition." 
</P>
