<HEADLINE> UK Orders Six Warplanes to Italy for NATO Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The British government Friday
ordered six Royal Air Forace (RAF) Jaguar ground attack aircraft
and one Tristar tanker to fly to Italy to prepare for a possible
NATO air exercise over Albania and Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
British Defense Secretary George Robertson said in a statement
issued Friday afternoon, "In the next 24 hours, the Jaguars will
fly to Gioia del Colle, Italy, from RAF Coltishall in Norfolk, and
the Tristar will fly to Ancona, Italy, from RAF Brize Norton."
</P>
<P>
Robertson noted that the exercise was not just "defense
ministers rattling sabers. It is time for Belgrade to get the
message that NATO means business."
</P>
<P>
"The purpose of the exercise is to demonstrate NATO's ability
to project air power into the area rapidly. A multinational NATO
air exercise will show Belgrade how high the stakes have become,"
he added.
</P>
<P>
The British defense chief also said that the exercise could
involve some 40 aircraft from more than six NATO countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
