<HEADLINE> More Sudanese Die of Meningitis This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
KHARTOUM, June 12 (Xinhua) -- There have been an upsurge of
meningitis in Sudan with 39 people having died of the disease so far
this year as against seven in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The Ra'i Al-Akhar daily here reported Friday that 299 meningitis
cases have been registered, with 125 of them among children below
age five.
</P>
<P>
Mohamed Qalandar, director of Epidemic Department of the Health
Ministry, said they have worked out a plan aimed at inoculating 3
million citizens annually against the disease.
</P>
<P>
Though the Finance Ministry failed to provide the 150 million
Sudanese pounds (about 78,900 U.S. dollars) as required by the
epidemic department for the inoculation for 400,000 Sudanese, the
Health Ministry has managed to distribute 75 million Sudanese pounds
(about 4,000 U.S. dollars) throughout the country for the
inoculation, Qalandar said.
</P>
<P>
And local health departments have been required to carry out
free inoculation for local residents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
