<HEADLINE> Cyprus Stock Market Edges up This Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, June 12 (Xinhua) -- The CISCO All-Share index of the
Cyprus Stock Market increased 9.5 points, or 2.2 percent in the past
trading week to close at 432.7 Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A market review issued by the Cyprus Investment and Securities
Corporation Limited (CISCO) said Friday the market sustained an
upward trend since June 3 following a three-week fall due to
traders' worries about the political uncertainty on the divided island.
</P>
<P>
On first trading day of the past week Tuesday (Monday was a
public holiday), the market remained firm at last Friday's closing
level, the following two days ended in positive ground.
</P>
<P>
But the average daily volume of transactions this week shrank to
4.1 million Cyprus pounds (about 8.2 million U.S. dollars), from
last week's 6 million pounds (about 12 million dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
